    ", x m in decreasing order of their respective scores s 1,.",
    "In addition to learning from object preferences, another important type of ranking problem is learning from label preferences.",
    "A key difference between object and label ranking concerns the formal representation of the preference context and the alternatives to be ordered.",
    "In object ranking, the context is (implicitly) assumed to be fixed, and hence not represented at all.",
    "What changes from one prediction task to the other is the set of objects to be ranked (e.g., red wines), and these objects are characterized in terms of associated properties."
